     1	//! Documented page-corruption tool for AC-006 fixture binding.
     2	//!
     3	//! AC-006 requires a deterministic page-corruption harness whose flavors
     4	//! map onto the two `code` values the engine surfaces from
     5	//! `(EventSource::SqliteInternal, EventCategory::Corruption)`:
     6	//!
     7	//! - [`corrupt_database_header`] — overwrites the SQLite magic-header
     8	//!   string at the start of the page at index 0 (the header-bearing
     9	//!   page). On reopen this surfaces `SQLITE_NOTADB`.
    10	//! - [`corrupt_interior_page_byte`] — XORs a single byte at a caller
    11	//!   chosen `(page_index, byte_offset)` outside the magic header. With
    12	//!   `byte_offset >= 100` on the page at index 0 (or any byte on a
    13	//!   page at index >= 1) this hits the SQLite B-tree decoder during
    14	//!   the `Engine::open` schema probe and surfaces `SQLITE_CORRUPT`.
    15	//!
    16	//! Both helpers operate on a CLOSED database file. They MUST NOT be
    17	//! called against an open SQLite handle: the harness writes raw bytes via
    18	//! `std::fs`, bypassing the page cache.
    19	//!
