   184	
   185	The table above is the only canonical materialized join for the open-path
   186	corruption contract in 0.6.0.
   187	
   188	### `CorruptionLocator` ownership
   189	
   190	`CorruptionLocator` keeps the broader locator enum even though `Engine.open`
   191	uses only a subset of variants today. Every variant remains justified:
   192	
   193	| `CorruptionLocator`                                     | Why it exists in 0.6.0                                                                                                                    |
   194	| ------------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
   195	| `FileOffset { offset: u64 }`                            | Header/page-byte diagnosis needs a byte-position locator that survives even when no logical row can be decoded.                           |
   196	| `PageId { page: u32 }`                                  | WAL replay and page-level diagnosis still produce page ids; this remains justified even after integrity-check removal from the open path. |
   197	| `TableRow { table: &'static str, rowid: i64 }`          | Schema and embedder-profile failures may be row-addressable even when the file is otherwise readable.                                     |
   198	| `Vec0ShadowRow { partition: &'static str, rowid: i64 }` | Doctor / recovery diagnostics may need to point at sqlite-vec shadow rows, which are not user-named tables.                               |
   199	| `MigrationStep { from: u32, to: u32 }`                  | Some failures are best localized to a migration edge rather than a page or row.                                                           |
   200	| `OpaqueSqliteError { sqlite_extended_code: i32 }`       | Required fallback when SQLite surfaces corruption without a usable structured locator; replaces any forbidden `Unspecified` escape hatch. |
