- `dev/plans/prompts/12-D-durability-harnesses.md` was not present in this checkout, so I could not compare against that prompt directly.
- `MEMORY.md` and the referenced `feedback_*.md` files were also not present in this worktree, so the output JSON’s TDD claim was not independently verifiable from repo files. The visible git history bundles tests and engine changes together, so red-before-green evidence is not recoverable from commit history alone.
- Review was static only. I did not execute the durability harnesses in this read-only sandbox.
